# Minutes of Meeting — Phase 3

Phase: Phase 3 — Training, Testing & Deployment  
Meeting No.: 3  
Date: 12-11-2025
Mode: In-person / Online  

## Attendees
- Abeer  
- Sufyan  
- AbuBakar  
- Ahmed Rafiq  


## Agenda
1. Review progress from Phase 2  
2. Plan Phase 3 implementation tasks  
3. Assign responsibilities for training, testing, and deployment  
4. Define expected outputs for Phase 3

## Discussion Summary

- Phase 2 tasks were reviewed and confirmed as completed, including repository setup, baseline NDVI work, and initial YOLO script drafting.
- It was agreed that Phase 3 will focus on **full-scale model training**, **NDVI/VARI evaluation**, and **Jetson Nano deployment**.
- YOLOv8-n will be trained on the complete PlantVillage dataset and evaluated using accuracy and loss metrics.
- NDVI and VARI outputs will be tested on SEN12MS samples and compared against ground truth NDVI.
- Jetson Nano setup will be completed, followed by real-time inference testing and FPS measurement.
- Results such as plots, graphs, and performance logs will be documented and stored in the `/results` directory.


## Decisions Made

- YOLOv8-n selected as the final detection model for deployment.
- RGB-based NDVI/VARI estimation to be used instead of multispectral hardware.
- TensorRT optimization will be applied for Jetson Nano inference.
- Phase 3 results will include both quantitative metrics and visual outputs.

---

